verbose_text: Enzyme linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) showed that serum levels of interleukin-1beta (IL-1beta), tumor necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-alpha), intercellular adhesion molecule-1 (ICAM-1), and vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) in the mouse model of PID were significantly increased compared with the control group, and that treatment with fukeqianjin, the xiaoyuningkun decoction, and Cynanchum paniculatum significantly inhibited the production of these cytokines in the mouse model (XREF_FIG).
evidence: levels of interleukin-1beta (IL-1beta), tumor necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-alpha), intercellular adhesion molecule-1
